US National Security Advisor Lieutenant General H.R. McMaster spoke with President Ashraf Ghani of Afghanistan to express condolences for the recent terrorist attacks in Kabul. McMaster condemned the attacks and reiterated the United States' support for the Afghan government and people. He emphasized the importance of unity in the face of adversity and expressed confidence in the Afghan people's ability to overcome this difficult period. McMaster also praised the bravery of the Afghan security forces in their efforts to combat terrorism.